==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Firstling
<hw>First"ling</hw> <pr>(f⟦etil⟧rst"l⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>First</ets> + <ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
first produce or offspring; -- said of animals, especially domestic
animals; <as>as, the <ex>firstlings</ex> of his flock</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The thing first thought or done.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The very <qex>firstlings</qex> of my heart shall be⟦br⟧
The <qex>firstlings</qex> of my hand.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firstling</ent>⟦br⟧

